			<p><strong>Date:</strong> Tuesday, October 20th (See schedule of events below)<br />
			<strong>Location:</strong> Rotunda in Mall of America (see <a href="http://www.mallofamerica.com/events/view/1292" target="_blank">web page</a> for event details)</p>
			
			<p>October is National Bullying Prevention Month, which was started by PACER Center in 2006, and YouTube sensation Bethany Mota will help mark the occasion Tuesday, Oct. 20 at Mall of America&reg; during PACER’s Together Against Bullying Day. Mota, who has more than 8 million subscribers on her YouTube channel and has been featured in &ldquo;TIME Magazine,&rdquo; on the Ellen DeGeneres Show and numerous other major media outlets, will share her personal experiences with bullying and participate in a Q&A session with 300 fans. Additionally, there will be a Viktor’s Quest to S.T.O.P. Bullying show in the Rotunda at 10 a.m. and 1:00 p.m. This event is presented by PACER’s National Bullying Prevention Center, with cosponsors the Minnesota Vikings, HopeLine&reg; from Verizon, and Mall of America.</p>
			
			<p>PACER&rsquo;s National Bullying  Prevention Center is joining with the Minnesota Vikings and HopeLine&reg;&nbsp;from  Verizon to host several activities during the day at Rotunda in Mall of America.  Viktor&rsquo;s Quest to S.T.O.P. Bullying is an interactive, educational bullying  prevention assembly that features Viktor, the Official Mascot of the Minnesota  Vikings, and an emcee live. The program includes interactive call-in guests  featuring Blair Walsh (Minnesota Vikings Player), Paul Allen (Vikings Radio  Network), and Minnesota Vikings Cheerleaders. There will be two presentations in  the Rotunda for students from Hilltop Elementary of Inver  Grove Heights.</p>
			
			<p>&ldquo;Bethany’s story has impacted countless teens around the world, and we are thrilled that she is coming to Mall of America to share it with her fans in Minnesota,&rdquo; said Julie Hertzog, director of PACER’s National Bullying Prevention Center. &ldquo;She has been an outstanding partner of PACER’s bullying prevention efforts through her school speaking tour, Inspiring Change, and the positive messages she shares with millions of followers on social media.&rdquo;</p>
						
					<h3 class="ExpandHeader" style="clear:left; margin-right:250px;">October 20th schedule of events</h3>
			
			<div class="ExpandItem OpenBorder" style="margin-right:250px">
			<p><strong>6:00 a.m.: Wristband distribution for Bethany Mota presentation – Rotunda</strong></p>
			<p>Mall of America staff will distribute 300 wristbands for Bethany’s presentation. See <a href="/bullying/getinvolved/pdf/Event Guidelines - Bethany Mota.pdf" target="_blank">event guidelines</a></p>
 
			<p><strong>10:00 a.m.: Viktor’s Quest to S.T.O.P. Bullying Show #1 – Rotunda</strong></p>
			<p>Audience is 350 Kindergarten through second grade students from Hilltop Elementary</p>
	
			<p><strong>1:00 p.m.: Viktor’s Quest to S.T.O.P. Bullying Show #2: Rotunda</strong></p>
			<p>Audience is 330 third to fifth grade students from Hilltop Elementary</p>
	
